  "texts": [
    "Vicuna RST p w -LoRA",
    "The cerebellum's role in movement and learning was explored in a study by Khilkevich et al., where rabbits were trained to blink in response to cues.",
    "This research investigated the cerebellum's capacity for associative learning and its ability to use internal feedback from one movement as a cue for the next.",
    "Findings revealed that rabbits could learn sequential blinking, with each blink triggering the subsequent one.",
    "This suggests that the cerebellum not only coordinates simple movements but can also chain complex sequences of movements together."
  ]
}